Question 3 answer:
&lt;br&gt;
If I understand you correctly, passing value, that is not reference or pointer to the function that takes reference will give this function direct access to this variable, or also fields of the actual value that you passed to this function.
Example:
```
void foo(int&amp; ref)
{
	ref = 5;
}

void bar(int non_ref)
{
	non_ref = 0;
}
int main()
{
	int integer_value = 1;
	foo(integer_value);
	bar(integer_value);

	return 0;
}
```
The first function will affect passed value, but the second won&#39;t, cause the operation of this function applied to copy of passed value.

